I"Ó<ul>
  <li>tl;dr:  <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">fdfind . | sad "locale" "localBLAH" --pager 'delta -s'</code> &lt;‚Äì use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">tab</code> to toggle select, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Y</code> to execute, affected files are printed to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">stdout</code></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="details">Details:</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">fdfind</code> is <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">fd</code> on macOS and other Unix systems. Ubuntu already has an <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">fd</code>command</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>I have no idea how to use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">vertico</code> in emacs. See ‚ÄúOriginal Checkvist‚Äù below :-)</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2 id="original-checkvist">Original Checkvist</h2>

<p>May 22, 2022 18:48 <a href="https://twitter.com/kjhealy/status/1528545478127779848">Today in Command line Fun for Some Values of Fun‚Ñ¢, combine <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">fzf</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sad</code> to switch out your venerable but somewhat perilous sed or perl one-liner that recursively finds &amp; replaces texts in files with a thing with a diff viewer that lets you preview what‚Äôs going to happen.</a> &lt;‚Äì <strong>tl;dr</strong>: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">fd "blah*.rb" | sad "old text" "new text" --pager s</code> ‚Äì&gt; <strong>QUOTE</strong> from followup tweet: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Side note to @ftrain: yes, OBVIOUSLY one should just do this in Emacs with vertico and C-c s p foo C-; E C-c C-p :%s/foo/bar/g RET Z Z</code> ‚Äì&gt; <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">fdfind</code> on ubuntu ‚Äì&gt; <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">fdfind . | sad "locale" "localBLAH" --pager 'delta -s'</code> &lt;‚Äì use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">tab</code> to toggle select, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Y</code> to execute, affected files are printed to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">stdout</code></p>

